## When to use
Use this skill when you need to check running processes on your system. This is useful for identifying resource usage by different processes or diagnosing performance issues.

## Approach
The `shell_exec` tool can be used to execute the `ps` command with various options to filter and sort process information. For example, `ps aux | grep <process_name>` allows you to find a specific process.

## Example
To list all running processes along with their resource usage:
```shell
shell_exec("ps aux")
```
This will provide an overview of each running process including its PID, CPU usage, memory usage, and the command it is executing.

## Pitfalls
- Be cautious when using `grep` in combination with `ps`, as it can sometimes include `grep` itself in the output.
- Using complex options with `ps` might require understanding of shell pipes (`|`) for filtering results effectively.